  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Adult learning theory distinguishes adult learners, such as STEM teachers, by emphasizing their autonomy, self-direction, and motivation to engage in learning that is relevant to their professional needs.",
    "Swanson (2018) noted that STEM teachers are autonomous learners who emphasize selfconcept as a key factor in adult learning.",
    "This study uses this concept to analyze how TPD programs can be tailored to support self-directed professional growth.",
    "Walker (2022) highlights the importance of developing TPD programs that encourage teachers to take ownership of their learning, thereby aligning TPD initiatives with the principles of adult learning theory.",
    "This theoretical perspective guides the analysis of TPD programs in China, particularly in evaluating how these programs address the diverse learning needs of STEM teachers."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Swanson (2018) noted that STEM teachers are autonomous learners who emphasize selfconcept as a key factor in adult learning.",
    "Walker (2022) highlights the importance of developing TPD programs that encourage teachers to take ownership of their learning, thereby aligning TPD initiatives with the principles of adult learning theory."
  ]
